{
  "texts": [
    "However, the performance of this method in large-scale unstructured environments has not been fully verified.",
    "Page 15 of 44 83 Cop et al. (2018) introduced DELIGHT, a highly efficient global localization descriptor that solely relies on LiDAR data without requiring robot motion information.",
    "This pioneering work leverages the LiDAR intensity image data and encodes it into a unique descriptor comprising a collection of histograms.",
    "DELIGHT stands out as the first solution that offers a near real-time approach to global localization by utilizing global intensity descriptors.",
    "Guo et al. (2019) introduced ISHOT, a local descriptor designed to enhance robust place recognition by integrating the advantages of both geometry and appearance using LiDAR intensity image data."
  ]
}